article.headline: Murray St. 52, Austin Peay 14
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. -- Casey Brockman completed 38 of 43 passes for 455 yards and five touchdowns to lead Murray State to a 52-14 victory against Austin Peay on Saturday night. Walter Powell caught nine passes for 172 yards and two touchdowns -- including one for 71 yards -- for Murray State (3-3, 2-1 Ohio Valley Conference). Dontel Watkins also caught two TD passes for the Racers. Backup KD Humphries was 2-for-2 passing with 30 yards and a score. Austin Peay (0-6, 0-4) scored 14 second-quarter points to close the gap to 17-14, but the Racers scored the next 35 points en route to amassing 549 total yards. Ten Murray State players caught passes, with four on the receiving end of touchdowns. Jake Ryan passed for 241 yards and a touchdown for Austin Peay, Devin Stark caught 10 passes for 125 yards and Reco Williams ran for 113 yards and a touchdown.
